The paper discusses a search engine and citation index for academic articles, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper discusses bibliometric analysis and search strategies for academic articles. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses searching for articles based on title, authors, and publication year. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.DB (Databases) are less likely but still possible as the paper discusses filtering out matches with dissimilar metadata and finding articles with DOIs. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper discusses using machine learning algorithms to improve search accuracy.
